Package: owea
Type: Package
Title: Optimal Weights Exchange Algorithm for Approximate Optimal Designs
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Min", "Yang", role = c("aut")),
    person("Stefanie", "Biedermann", role = "aut"),
    person("Elvis", "Tang", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "alex.tang.yang@gmail.com"))
Description: Finds D- and A-optimal approximate designs for linear, nonlinear
    and generalized linear models using the Optimal Weights Exchange Algorithm
    (OWEA) of Yang, Biedermann and Tang (2013)
    <doi:10.1080/01621459.2013.806268>. The model enters the algorithm through
    a single per-point function returning EITHER the information vector
    f(x, theta) (per-point information matrix = f f', the fast path) OR the full
    k-by-k information matrix at x (the general path). A single C++ core
    (RcppArmadillo) handles both representations. Supports D- and A-optimality,
    general differentiable functions g(theta) of the parameters, multistage
    designs that augment an existing design, sequential (coarse-to-fine) grid
    search, and optional merging of neighbouring support points.
